Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A.1(c) | Description :Establish, at least two Regional Operating Units reportingadministratively to the PCT | Due Date :31-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.C | Description :Prepare and furnish to the Association detailed annual operating plans |Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section III.D | Description :Procurement audits to be carried out by independent auditors |Frequency :Yearly

(b) of Schedule 2 | Description :Prior to the implementation of Subprojects, the Recipientthrough EMPODERAR shall, upon having selected a Community Investment Subproject, enter into a written agreement with each Communityor cluster thereof, as the case may be, for the provision of the respective Community Investment Grant, on terms and conditionsacceptable to the Association. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

title.narrative: Improved access to basic infrastructure and services in targeted communities

target.value: Additional 3 months of road access per year; 1,400 ha irrigated (new and improved); 480 km of fences constructed; additional 400m3per day safe drinking water available for targeted communities

actual.value: 3.0 Additional months of road access per year (corresponding to 129 communities with improved rural road access during the rainyseason); 2,611 ha irrigated (new and improved); 2,809 km of fences constructed; additional 523 m3 per day of safe drinking wateravailable for targeted communities
